data.description:
Back on the market again!  Wondering why it's been online so long, we have had multiple contracts accepted, with multiple financing issues.  This is a Modern Sanctuary by Wyandotte Park As dawn breaks, the first rays of sun illuminate the corner lot of Beecher St., revealing a home that tells a tale of modern charm and rustic elegance. Just across the street, the serene expanse of Wyandotte Park stands as a daily invitation to take a leisurely stroll or a refreshing jog. The moment you step onto this property, the hardwood floors greet you with a warmth that whispers tales of countless cozy evenings. Wander further in and you're embraced by a sitting room, perfect for storytelling sessions with friends or quiet moments with a book. The heart of this abode, the kitchen, is a blend of contemporary and classic. Stainless appliances shine amidst the rustic ambiance, and an island awaits, ready for morning coffee chats or midnight snack runs.

And there's a twist! What now serves as a delightful living room, with exposed bricks revealing snippets of its history, can easily transform back into a second bedroom, depending on your narrative.

Outside, the backyard beckons. Raised garden beds stand ready for green-thumbed adventures, all the while ensuring utmost privacy. A detached garage sits patiently, ready for its next journey, while the fenced front and backyard promise playful days for your pets.

Come, be a part of this story. A modern sanctuary, a stone's throw from nature, awaits its next chapter.
